  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And here is a blueprint of it all.' And I drew a little picture there of, actually, how I found the buildings at the camp. 'As you can see, it was a house of murder where human beings were pushed alive into one entrance and came out dead at the other.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Some bodies were burned-- those in room number one.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were three big furnaces in room number two filled with human bones.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in room number three were supposed to-- those that were supposed to have been buried, 500 into one common grave.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There wasn't enough coal to burn all the people they killed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Anyway, they never got around to burn or bury them all before we came because our troops got there before the SS expected us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Both rooms are still filled high with gassed, shot, hanged, and tortured dead bodies, a sight I shall never forget.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Most all bodies in the room number three were dressed in prison clothing, striped suits.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Yet, but all bodies in room number one were naked.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh darling, it was a horrible sight.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The gas chamber was a room with airtight steel doors labeled, shower bath.' [NON-ENGLISH], what do they call it?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whatever. 'They were regular shower heads built into the ceiling, but poison gas came out of these instead of water.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were thousands of suits taken from the dead piled in the back yard.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Yugoslav slave I talked to said that he alone had been forced to burn more than 2,500 persons, he alone, during the last months.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They never worked more than a month or two in the furnace rooms.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, they were either killed themselves or sent to a different concentration camp, after a month of 24 hours a day 'steady work' quote, unquote.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
